(0, 'What would you show a first-time visitor to {place}?\n---\nNot the guidebook version, the real one.\n• A backyard, a diner, a view only locals know\n• What would they need to see to understand it?\n• Who would you bring along?', 'place', '{place}', 'hometown', 'place', '{has_places}', 'hometown_intro', '{hometown,neighborhood}', 51),
(0, 'What did {place} actually smell like?\n---\nNot the postcard version, the real one.\n• The air after rain, a bakery on a certain block\n• The way the seasons changed\n• What hits you first when you remember?', 'place', '{place}', 'sensory', 'feeling', '{has_places}', 'place_smell', '{sensory,hometown}', 52),
(0, 'Who from {place} do you still wonder about?\n---\nSomeone you lost touch with but never forgot.\n• A neighbor, a classmate, someone you saw around\n• What do you remember about them?\n• What would you ask if you ran into them?', 'place', '{place}', 'connections', 'people', '{has_places}', 'place_person_lost', '{friendship,hometown}', 53),
(0, 'What spot in {place} has changed beyond recognition?\n---\nPicture it the way it was.\n• A store, a hangout, a corner that mattered\n• What would someone miss who never saw it?\n• When did it change?', 'place', '{place}', 'nostalgia', 'place', '{has_places}', 'vanished_spot', '{nostalgia,change}', 54),
(0, 'What was your favorite time of day in {place}?\n---\nEvery place has a golden hour.\n• Early morning, before dinner, late at night\n• What made that hour yours?\n• What were you usually doing?', 'place', '{place}', 'routine', 'feeling', '{has_places}', 'place_time_of_day', '{routine,peace}', 55),
(0, 'What''s something about {place} only residents understood?\n---\nEvery place has its insider knowledge.\n• A shortcut, an unspoken rule, a thing everyone just knew\n• Would an outsider ever figure it out?\n• What comes to mind first?', 'place', '{place}', 'insider', 'place', '{has_places}', 'place_insider', '{local,secrets}', 56),
(0, 'What kind of weather in {place} sticks in your memory?\n---\nWeather can define a place as much as anything.\n• A snowstorm, an endless summer, a certain wind\n• What was happening in your life during it?\n• Can you still feel it?', 'place', '{place}', 'sensory', 'feeling', '{has_places}', 'place_weather', '{weather,sensory,seasons}', 57),
(0, 'Where did you go in {place} when you needed to be alone?\n---\nEveryone has a retreat, even if nobody else sees it.\n• A park bench, a room, a spot no one else valued\n• What did it look like?\n• What were you usually working through?', 'place', '{place}', 'solitude', 'place', '{has_places}', 'place_alone_spot', '{solitude,retreat}', 58),
(0, 'What food was specific to {place} that you can''t find elsewhere?\n---\nSome flavors belong to one place only.\n• A dish at a local spot, a neighbor''s recipe\n• What was it?\n• Who did you eat it with?', 'place', '{place}', 'food', 'object', '{has_places}', 'place_food', '{food,hometown,nostalgia}', 59),
