(2, 'What song can''t you hear without thinking of {person_name}?\n---\nMusic and people become inseparable.\n• It played at their house, in their car, at a shared moment\n• What''s the song?\n• What version of them does it bring back?', 'person', '{person_name}', 'music', 'object', '{has_contacts,answered_5+}', 'person_song', '{music,association}', 275),
(2, 'When were you genuinely proud of someone, not politely, deeply?\n---\nReal pride for someone else is its own feeling.\n• A child, a friend, a parent stepping up\n• What did they do?\n• What was that pride like in your chest?', NULL, '{}', 'pride', 'feeling', '{answered_5+}', 'proud_of_other', '{pride,love}', 276),
(2, 'What goodbye have you had to say more than once?\n---\nSome farewells keep happening.\n• Long distance, recurring airport goodbyes, a slow loss\n• What was it?\n• How did you carry it?', NULL, '{}', 'loss', 'event', '{answered_5+}', 'repeated_goodbye', '{loss,endurance}', 277),
(2, 'What holiday went off the rails and became better for it?\n---\nChaos sometimes brings people closer.\n• The turkey burned, someone showed up unannounced\n• Plans fell apart in the best way\n• Why was the mess better than the plan?', NULL, '{}', 'holidays', 'event', '{answered_5+}', 'holiday_offscript', '{holidays,chaos,joy}', 278),
(2, 'What did {person_name} teach you that they never meant to?\n---\nThe most important lessons are accidental.\n• Patience, honesty, handling disappointment\n• What did you absorb just by watching?\n• Do they know?', 'person', '{person_name}', 'lessons', 'people', '{has_contacts,answered_5+}', 'person_accidental_lesson', '{lessons,modeling}', 279),
(2, 'When did you forgive someone before you were truly ready?\n---\nSometimes the decision outpaces the feeling.\n• The situation called for it, or you wanted to move forward\n• How did it feel?\n• Did forgiveness eventually catch up?', NULL, '{}', 'forgiveness', 'turning_point', '{answered_5+}', 'early_forgiveness', '{forgiveness,process}', 280),
(2, 'What community shaped you more than you expected?\n---\nBelonging changes us.\n• A church, a team, a neighborhood, coworkers\n• What role did you play?\n• What did belonging there give you?', NULL, '{}', 'community', 'people', '{answered_5+}', 'shaping_community', '{community,identity}', 281),
(2, 'What piece of art said something you couldn''t put into words?\n---\nArt gives voice to wordless feelings.\n• Music, writing, a painting\n• What did it capture?\n• What did it finally give language to?', NULL, '{}', 'expression', 'object', '{answered_5+}', 'art_spoke', '{expression,resonance}', 282),
(2, 'When was just being there for someone in pain the whole thing?\n---\nPresence can be more powerful than solutions.\n• You didn''t fix it, just stayed\n• Who was it, what were they going through?\n• What was that like?', NULL, '{}', 'presence', 'event', '{answered_5+}', 'sitting_with_pain', '{presence,compassion}', 283),
(2, 'Where do you do your best thinking?\n---\nEveryone has a place where their mind opens up.\n• A porch, a trail, the shower, a chair\n• What does it look like?\n• Why does it work?', NULL, '{}', 'reflection', 'place', '{answered_5+}', 'thinking_spot', '{reflection,solitude}', 284),
(2, 'When did you choose kindness when it would have been easier not to?\n---\nKindness under pressure is the real test.\n• Tired, hurt, or justified in being harsh\n• What made you choose the harder path?\n• Did the other person know the cost?', NULL, '{}', 'character', 'event', '{answered_5+}', 'chose_kindness', '{character,integrity}', 285),
(2, 'What secret do you and {person_name} share that still makes you smile?\n---\nShared secrets are their own kind of love.\n• Harmless, maybe a little mischievous, but yours\n• What is it?\n• What does it say about your bond?', 'person', '{person_name}', 'secrets', 'people', '{has_contacts,answered_5+}', 'person_secret', '{secrets,bonding}', 286),
(2, 'When did you see your parent as just a person figuring it out?\n---\nThis shift changes everything.\n• They told you something from before you existed\n• Or you caught a look that showed something new\n• What did you see?', NULL, '{}', 'family', 'turning_point', '{answered_5+}', 'parent_as_person', '{family,empathy}', 287),
(2, 'What scent takes you to a specific moment with a specific person?\n---\nSmell is the fastest time machine.\n• Their cologne, a food they made, the air of a shared place\n• What is the scent?\n• Where does it drop you?', NULL, '{}', 'sensory', 'feeling', '{answered_5+}', 'scent_person', '{sensory,association}', 288),
(2, 'What did you build or fix that solved a problem nobody else even saw?\n---\nQuiet problem-solving is its own reward.\n• A system, a repair, a creative workaround\n• What was the problem?\n• What was satisfying about being the one?', NULL, '{}', 'resourcefulness', 'object', '{answered_5+}', 'problem_solved', '{resourcefulness,creativity}', 289),
(2, 'What does {person_name}''s handwriting look like?\n---\nHandwriting is personality on paper.\n• On a card, a list, a note left on the counter\n• Rushed, careful, messy, distinctive\n• What does it tell you about them?', 'person', '{person_name}', 'detail', 'people', '{has_contacts,answered_5+}', 'person_handwriting', '{detail,character}', 290),
(2, 'When did you put something in writing because you couldn''t say it out loud?\n---\nWriting can hold what speaking can''t.\n• A letter, a text, something you wrote and never sent\n• What did you need to express?\n• Why did writing feel safer?', NULL, '{}', 'expression', 'event', '{answered_5+}', 'written_not_spoken', '{expression,vulnerability}', 291),
(2, 'What place holds a specific emotion for you?\n---\nPlaces can carry feelings.\n• A hallway that feels like anticipation, a park like grief\n• Where is it?\n• What emotion lives there?', NULL, '{}', 'association', 'place', '{answered_5+}', 'emotion_place', '{association,feeling}', 292),
(2, 'What''s the strangest coincidence that ever happened to you?\n---\nSome things feel like the universe is paying attention.\n• Two unrelated things converged impossibly\n• What happened?\n• Did it change how you think about chance?', NULL, '{}', 'fate', 'event', '{answered_5+}', 'strange_coincidence', '{fate,wonder}', 293),
(2, 'When did someone''s face tell you everything before they spoke?\n---\nFaces can say what words won''t.\n• Joy, heartbreak, guilt, relief\n• Whose face was it?\n• What did their expression reveal?', NULL, '{}', 'perception', 'people', '{answered_5+}', 'face_told_all', '{perception,truth}', 294),
(2, 'When did you change your mind mid-action, and it ended up mattering?\n---\nPivots can be the most important moves.\n• Turned the car around, rewrote a message, backed out\n• What made you shift?\n• What came of it?', NULL, '{}', 'pivots', 'turning_point', '{answered_5+}', 'mid_pivot', '{pivots,courage}', 295),
(2, 'What gift from {person_name} was so perfect it almost hurt?\n---\nBeing truly known through a gift is intense.\n• They''d been paying attention, remembering something\n• What was the gift?\n• What did it say about how they see you?', 'person', '{person_name}', 'gifts', 'object', '{has_contacts,answered_5+}', 'person_gift', '{gifts,being_known}', 296),
(2, 'What neighborhood sound from your past would unlock a flood of memories?\n---\nSounds carry whole worlds.\n• An ice cream truck, a specific bird, children playing\n• What is the sound?\n• What comes rushing back?', NULL, '{}', 'sensory', 'feeling', '{answered_5+}', 'neighborhood_sound', '{sensory,nostalgia}', 297),
(2, 'What family object carries more weight than its size?\n---\nHeirlooms hold invisible gravity.\n• A ring, a photograph, a tool, furniture\n• Who did it belong to?\n• What story does it hold?', NULL, '{}', 'heritage', 'object', '{answered_5+}', 'family_heirloom', '{heritage,weight}', 298),
(2, 'When did someone show you grace you didn''t deserve?\n---\nUnearned kindness transforms us.\n• You''d made a mistake, let someone down\n• Who extended the grace?\n• What did it do to you?', NULL, '{}', 'grace', 'feeling', '{answered_5+}', 'undeserved_grace', '{grace,humility}', 299),
(2, 'When was {person_name} the most alive you''ve ever seen them?\n---\nWatching someone be fully themselves is magnetic.\n• In their element, laughing hard, absorbed in a moment\n• What were they doing?\n• What was it like to watch?', 'person', '{person_name}', 'vitality', 'people', '{has_contacts,answered_5+}', 'person_alive', '{vitality,essence}', 300),
(2, 'What sound from nature has personal meaning for you?\n---\nNature''s sounds carry individual stories.\n• Rain on a roof, waves, wind through trees\n• What is the sound?\n• What feeling does it carry?', NULL, '{}', 'nature', 'feeling', '{answered_5+}', 'nature_sound', '{nature,meaning}', 301),
(2, 'What boundary changed a relationship for the better?\n---\nBoundaries can heal what closeness alone can''t.\n• Hard to draw, the other person didn''t like it at first\n• What was the boundary?\n• How did things shift?', NULL, '{}', 'boundaries', 'turning_point', '{answered_5+}', 'healthy_boundary', '{boundaries,growth}', 302),
(2, 'When did public embarrassment turn into something wonderful?\n---\nSome of the best stories start with mortification.\n• The attention shifted, someone rescued you\n• The mistake opened an unexpected door\n• What happened?', NULL, '{}', 'embarrassment', 'event', '{answered_5+}', 'embarrassment_win', '{embarrassment,redemption}', 303),
(2, 'What was the last conversation with {person_name} that really mattered?\n---\nNot small talk, something with weight.\n• What were you talking about, what was at stake?\n• Did you both walk away feeling settled or opened up?\n• What was said?', 'person', '{person_name}', 'depth', 'people', '{has_contacts,answered_5+}', 'person_deep_talk', '{depth,connection}', 304),
(2, 'What color do you associate with a specific time in your life?\n---\nEras have palettes.\n• College was blue, your thirties were gold\n• What''s the color, what''s the era?\n• What connects them?', NULL, '{}', 'synesthesia', 'feeling', '{answered_5+}', 'era_color', '{synesthesia,association}', 305),
(2, 'What ritual keeps you grounded?\n---\nRoutines can be anchors.\n• Morning, evening, or seasonal\n• What is it, how did it start?\n• What would be missing without it?', NULL, '{}', 'ritual', 'event', '{answered_5+}', 'grounding_ritual', '{ritual,stability}', 306),
(2, 'Whose speaking voice is the most beautiful you''ve heard?\n---\nNot singing, just talking.\n• The tone, the pace, how they shaped words\n• Whose voice was it?\n• What was it like to listen?', NULL, '{}', 'beauty', 'people', '{answered_5+}', 'beautiful_voice', '{beauty,presence}', 307),
(2, 'When did someone you barely knew show up for you in a big way?\n---\nUnexpected support leaves a deep mark.\n• Offered help, said what you needed, made a gesture\n• Who were they?\n• Did you ever get to thank them?', NULL, '{}', 'unexpected', 'people', '{answered_5+}', 'acquaintance_showed_up', '{unexpected,kindness}', 308),
(2, 'What physical sensation triggers a specific memory?\n---\nThe body remembers what the mind files away.\n• Warmth, cold, wind, water on skin\n• What''s the sensation?\n• Where does it put you?', NULL, '{}', 'sensory', 'feeling', '{answered_5+}', 'physical_trigger', '{sensory,memory}', 309),
(2, 'When did you have to be the strong one?\n---\nHolding it together has a cost.\n• Everyone was falling apart, someone needed you\n• What did being strong look like?\n• What did it cost afterward?', NULL, '{}', 'strength', 'event', '{answered_5+}', 'being_strong', '{strength,cost}', 310),
(2, 'When did you and {person_name} not need to say anything at all?\n---\nSome silence is the fullest kind.\n• Just being in the same space was enough\n• What were you doing, where were you?\n• What made it feel full?', 'person', '{person_name}', 'presence', 'people', '{has_contacts,answered_5+}', 'person_presence', '{presence,comfort}', 311),
(2, 'What scene from your life could be a painting?\n---\nSome moments have perfect composition.\n• Light on a table, a figure in a doorway, a landscape\n• What would the painting show?\n• What would the title be?', NULL, '{}', 'beauty', 'place', '{answered_5+}', 'painting_scene', '{beauty,composition}', 312),
(2, 'When did your intuition save you from something?\n---\nGut feelings exist for a reason.\n• Changed plans at the last minute, trusted a feeling\n• What was the situation?\n• What would have happened otherwise?', NULL, '{}', 'intuition', 'event', '{answered_5+}', 'intuition_saved', '{intuition,trust}', 313),
(2, 'When did someone treat you as their safe place?\n---\nBeing someone''s shelter is a quiet honor.\n• They came to you scared, confused, or hurting\n• Who was it, what did they need?\n• What was it like to be that person?', NULL, '{}', 'caregiving', 'feeling', '{answered_5+}', 'safe_place', '{caregiving,responsibility}', 314),
(2, 'What''s the most meaningful thing you''ve inherited?\n---\nNot necessarily the most expensive.\n• A recipe card, a watch, a quilt, a habit\n• Who did it come from?\n• What does it carry that money can''t buy?', NULL, '{}', 'inheritance', 'object', '{answered_5+}', 'meaningful_inheritance', '{inheritance,legacy}', 315),
(2, 'What day started ordinary and became unforgettable?\n---\nThe best stories come from unexpected turns.\n• What were you expecting?\n• What actually happened?\n• When did you realize the day had changed?', NULL, '{}', 'surprise', 'event', '{answered_5+}', 'ordinary_to_unforgettable', '{surprise,fate}', 316),
(2, 'How does {person_name} show love without ever saying it?\n---\nActions speak louder than declarations.\n• Making sure you eat, checking the locks, a look across a room\n• What''s their love language in action?\n• Do they know you notice?', 'person', '{person_name}', 'love_language', 'people', '{has_contacts,answered_5+}', 'person_love_language', '{love_language,actions}', 317),
(2, 'What conversation changed the direction of your career or life?\n---\nSome words are turning points.\n• In an office, over dinner, with a stranger\n• What was said, who said it?\n• Did you know it mattered in the moment?', NULL, '{}', 'pivots', 'event', '{answered_5+}', 'direction_convo', '{pivots,influence}', 318),
(2, 'What texture brings back a memory when you touch it?\n---\nTouch has its own archive.\n• A fabric, the grain of wood, cool stone\n• What is the texture?\n• What were you feeling last time it mattered?', NULL, '{}', 'sensory', 'feeling', '{answered_5+}', 'texture_memory', '{sensory,touch}', 319),
(2, 'When did you let go of what you wanted so someone else could have what they needed?\n---\nSacrifice is quiet and powerful.\n• A dream set aside, a path stepped off\n• What did you give up?\n• Was it worth it?', NULL, '{}', 'sacrifice', 'turning_point', '{answered_5+}', 'letting_go', '{sacrifice,love}', 320),
(2, 'When did {person_name} stand up for you?\n---\nBeing defended changes how you see someone.\n• Public or quiet, maybe they had something to lose\n• What happened?\n• What did it tell you about who they are?', 'person', '{person_name}', 'defense', 'people', '{has_contacts,answered_5+}', 'person_stood_up', '{defense,loyalty}', 321),
(2, 'What door are you glad you walked through, even though you were nervous?\n---\nThe best things are often on the other side of fear.\n• A move, a conversation, a first step\n• What was on the other side?\n• How different would things be if you''d stayed?', NULL, '{}', 'decisions', 'turning_point', '{answered_5+}', 'glad_walked_through', '{decisions,courage}', 322),
(2, 'What night sky do you remember?\n---\nStars have a way of making us honest.\n• Camping, a rooftop, a field\n• Who was with you?\n• What were you thinking about?', NULL, '{}', 'nature', 'place', '{answered_5+}', 'night_sky', '{nature,wonder}', 323),
(2, 'What''s the bravest thing you''ve ever said to someone?\n---\nSome words take everything you have.\n• A truth held back, a confession, words that could change things\n• What did you say, who to?\n• What happened in the silence after?', NULL, '{}', 'courage', 'event', '{answered_5+}', 'bravest_words', '{courage,truth}', 324),
(2, 'When did helping someone change you more than it changed them?\n---\nGiving can transform the giver.\n• The act opened something\n• You saw yourself differently through their eyes\n• What shifted in you?', NULL, '{}', 'service', 'event', '{answered_5+}', 'helping_changed_me', '{service,transformation}', 325),
(2, 'What object from {person_name} do you still keep close?\n---\nObjects become proxies for people.\n• A letter, a tool, jewelry, something they''d be surprised you saved\n• What is it, where do you keep it?\n• What does holding it feel like?', 'person', '{person_name}', 'keepsakes', 'object', '{has_contacts,answered_5+}', 'person_keepsake', '{keepsakes,connection}', 326),
(2, 'When did you realize you were repeating a pattern from your family?\n---\nFamily echoes can surprise us.\n• How you argued, showed love, handled stress\n• When did you notice?\n• Did you keep it or break it?', NULL, '{}', 'patterns', 'turning_point', '{answered_5+}', 'family_pattern', '{patterns,awareness}', 327),
(2, 'When did laughter break the tension when nothing else could?\n---\nHumor is the ultimate tension release.\n• A funeral, an argument, a terrifying moment\n• What made everyone laugh?\n• What did it do to the room?', NULL, '{}', 'humor', 'event', '{answered_5+}', 'laughter_rescue', '{humor,relief}', 328),
(2, 'When did you witness beauty that felt like it was just for you?\n---\nPrivate beauty has a special quality.\n• Nobody else was around or noticed\n• What did you see?\n• What was it like to hold it alone?', NULL, '{}', 'wonder', 'feeling', '{answered_5+}', 'private_beauty', '{wonder,presence}', 329),
(2, 'What mundane errand became an adventure because of who you were with?\n---\nThe right person makes everything better.\n• Grocery shopping, the hardware store, something boring\n• What happened?\n• Who made it fun?', NULL, '{}', 'companionship', 'event', '{answered_5+}', 'errand_adventure', '{companionship,spontaneity}', 330),
(2, 'What did {person_name} smell like, not perfume, their actual presence?\n---\nScent is the most intimate sense.\n• Their house, their car, the air around them\n• What was the scent?\n• What feelings does it bring back?', 'person', '{person_name}', 'sensory', 'feeling', '{has_contacts,answered_5+}', 'person_scent', '{sensory,intimacy}', 331),
(2, 'What question from a child stopped you in your tracks?\n---\nChildren ask the questions adults avoid.\n• Simple, profound, or accidentally brilliant\n• What did they ask?\n• What would you say now more honestly?', NULL, '{}', 'children', 'event', '{answered_5+}', 'child_question', '{children,wisdom}', 332),
(2, 'When did choosing to be vulnerable change a relationship entirely?\n---\nVulnerability can be the bravest move.\n• Admitted something, asked for help, let someone see you\n• What happened?\n• How did they respond?', NULL, '{}', 'vulnerability', 'turning_point', '{answered_5+}', 'chose_vulnerable', '{vulnerability,change}', 333),
(2, 'When did you drive or walk somewhere just to clear your head?\n---\nMovement processes what the mind can''t.\n• Where did you go?\n• What was spinning?\n• Did the movement help?', NULL, '{}', 'processing', 'event', '{answered_5+}', 'clearing_head', '{processing,movement}', 334),
(2, 'What word or phrase only makes sense between you and someone you love?\n---\nPrivate language is its own intimacy.\n• From a joke, a mishearing, a private moment\n• What is it, how did it start?\n• What does having it mean?', NULL, '{}', 'language', 'people', '{answered_5+}', 'private_language', '{language,intimacy}', 335),
(2, 'What''s the most peaceful sound you can imagine?\n---\nPeace has a soundtrack.\n• Nature, someone breathing, a specific quiet\n• What is it?\n• When did you last hear it?', NULL, '{}', 'peace', 'feeling', '{answered_5+}', 'peaceful_sound', '{peace,sensory}', 336),
(2, 'When did someone you looked up to let you down?\n---\nDisillusionment is a kind of growing up.\n• They made a mistake, showed an unexpected side\n• What happened?\n• Did you ever see them the same?', NULL, '{}', 'disillusion', 'people', '{answered_5+}', 'let_down', '{disillusion,maturity}', 337),
(2, 'What old ticket, receipt, or stub did you save without knowing why?\n---\nPaper artifacts hold invisible weight.\n• In a drawer, a box, between pages\n• What is it, what does it mark?\n• What would you lose if you threw it away?', NULL, '{}', 'artifacts', 'object', '{answered_5+}', 'saved_artifact', '{artifacts,nostalgia}', 338),
(2, 'What conversation with {person_name} do you wish had gone differently?\n---\nWe all have conversations we''d rewrite.\n• Said the wrong thing, held back, missed a chance\n• What would you change?\n• What might the different version have opened?', 'person', '{person_name}', 'regret', 'people', '{has_contacts,answered_5+}', 'person_wish_convo', '{regret,honesty}', 339),
(2, 'What tradition ended, and should someone bring it back?\n---\nSome endings aren''t necessary.\n• Faded naturally, someone moved, life shifted\n• What was it, what killed it?\n• Could it be revived?', NULL, '{}', 'endings', 'event', '{answered_5+}', 'ended_tradition', '{endings,reflection}', 340),
(2, 'When did you feel the furthest from home?\n---\nDistance isn''t always about miles.\n• Could be across the world or in your own kitchen\n• What created the distance?\n• What brought you back?', NULL, '{}', 'distance', 'feeling', '{answered_5+}', 'far_from_home', '{distance,loneliness}', 341),
(2, 'When did you realize you were no longer the younger generation?\n---\nThis shift sneaks up on everyone.\n• A reference went over someone''s head\n• You said something your parents would say\n• How did it feel?', NULL, '{}', 'aging', 'turning_point', '{answered_5+}', 'generational_shift', '{aging,perspective}', 342),
(2, 'What meal do you remember for what happened around the table?\n---\nThe food is secondary to the moment.\n• A conversation, a revelation, an argument\n• Who was there?\n• Why does the dinner stay with you?', NULL, '{}', 'food', 'event', '{answered_5+}', 'table_event', '{food,gathering}', 343),
(2, 'How have you been misunderstood in a way that still bothers you?\n---\nMisunderstandings can sting for years.\n• An assumption people make that isn''t true\n• A version of your story that misses the point\n• What would you correct?', NULL, '{}', 'identity', 'feeling', '{answered_5+}', 'misunderstood', '{identity,frustration}', 344),
(2, 'What garden, park, or piece of land holds meaning in your life?\n---\nLand and memory go deep together.\n• You planted it, walked it, grew up beside it\n• What happened there?\n• What does the earth represent to you?', NULL, '{}', 'nature', 'place', '{answered_5+}', 'meaningful_land', '{nature,roots}', 345),
(2, 'When did holding someone''s hand say everything that needed saying?\n---\nTouch can be its own conversation.\n• Comfort, a promise, a goodbye, a beginning\n• Whose hand was it?\n• What passed between you?', NULL, '{}', 'touch', 'event', '{answered_5+}', 'hand_holding', '{touch,understanding}', 346),
(2, 'When did you have to say the thing nobody else would?\n---\nSomeone has to break the silence.\n• The room was avoiding it, people were tiptoeing\n• What did you say?\n• What happened after?', NULL, '{}', 'courage', 'event', '{answered_5+}', 'hard_truth_teller', '{courage,honesty}', 347),
(2, 'What''s the most comforting thing anyone said during a hard time?\n---\nThe right words at the right time can save us.\n• Not profound, just perfectly right\n• What were the words, who said them?\n• What did they give you?', NULL, '{}', 'comfort', 'feeling', '{answered_5+}', 'comforting_words', '{comfort,care}', 348),
(2, 'When did you catch yourself becoming someone you didn''t want to be?\n---\nSelf-awareness arrives at important moments.\n• A pattern, a reaction, a role you slipped into\n• What did you see?\n• What did you do about it?', NULL, '{}', 'self_awareness', 'turning_point', '{answered_5+}', 'caught_myself', '{self_awareness,course_correction}', 349),
(2, 'What lucky break changed your life?\n---\nSome of the best things happen by chance.\n• A meeting, perfect timing, an opportunity from nowhere\n• What happened?\n• How different would things be without it?', NULL, '{}', 'fortune', 'event', '{answered_5+}', 'lucky_break', '{fortune,gratitude}', 350);
